data.title: WESTERN ISO 8859-1 encoding not working once upgading to Atom 1.17.0
data.body:
After upgrading to Atom 1.17.0, file encoding for Western ISO 8859-1 is broke.  Characters that used to show correctly are now replaced with �.  

So, at Atom 1.16.0, a line of code would look like this:
IF VAR1 ¬= VAR2 THEN
Once upgrading to 1.17.0, we now see:
IF VAR1 �= VAR2 THEN

Other editors show the code correctly with the codepage set to ISO 8859-1.

data.title: Don't snapshot the `iconv-lite` module
data.body:
Fixes https://github.com/atom/encoding-selector/issues/48.

When deciding which methods to export, `iconv-lite` verifies the availability of some Node features, which is clearly an unsupported behavior when executing it via `mksnapshot`.

In this case we were not getting any exception at compile-time, but we noticed some methods were missing from iconv-lite's API. With this commit we are excluding this module from the snapshot, thus making all of its methods available again.

/cc: @iolsen
